{"session_id":"svc-1783127651982635375","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-07-04T01:14:14.889412022Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"sonnet","sticky":{"key_present":true,"assignment":"not_applicable","bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"sonnet","work_dir":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-53df5e2f-20260704T011321-22621c3e","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead in an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the contract: every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Too big if any holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, use a split-first pass.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, children once more; reject third-level splits with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child (copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add` only for legitimate child-to-child or sibling/replacement edges; never the parent.\u0026#xA;3. Use `parent=\u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` metadata and wire `parent -\u0026gt; child`.\u0026#xA;4. Write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path with child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Decomposition alone is success. Don\u0026#39;t mix it with implementation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC to concrete evidence (test, file, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Run git/index mutations sequentially; don\u0026#39;t parallelize `git add`, `git commit`, or staging/commit commands.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- If `lefthook run pre-commit` depends on staged files, rerun it after staging the exact commit set. A `no-staged-files` run is not acceptance evidence.\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; subject ends with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- Current-bead lifecycle is orchestrator-owned. Do not run `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --claim`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --status \u0026lt;status\u0026gt;`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --unclaim`, or `ddx bead close \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;`. Step 0 allows `ddx bead create`, `ddx bead dep add` for child-to-child or sibling/replacement edges, and `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path before exiting. No commit or rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The `no_changes_rationale.txt` file under the bead metadata `bundle` path must contain one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;For orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Reports go under the bead metadata `bundle` path in `.ddx/executions/`. **Never write reports to `/tmp` or outside the repo**. Use a named in-repo path when given; otherwise write `\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md` there. Commit it with the code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other instruction files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Long-running matrix/benchmark beads\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;For expensive commands (benchmarks, load tests, validation \u0026gt; 60s per variant):\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Write a matrix plan before launching expensive commands: list required configs, output paths, completion criteria.\u0026#xA;- Do not re-run the same long-running command unless: (1) the command fingerprint changed (args/env/config), AND (2) you document why prior output is invalid and what changed.\u0026#xA;- If a long-running command times out or is incomplete, exit with `status: open` + retryable `reason` in `no_changes_rationale.txt`. Do not silently retry; let the orchestrator decide.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-53df5e2f\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eIMP: JSONL→Postgres importer for production AxonStore migration (replaces legacy MigrateToAxon)\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\n# PROBLEM\u0026#xA;The legacy `*Store.MigrateToAxon` method (now exposed via `Migrator.MigrateToAxon` in MIG bead, returning `ErrDeprecated`) writes JSONL files under `.ddx/axon/` rather than performing an actual JSONL→Postgres migration. Per the audit in `docs/plans/plan-2026-05-10-axon-only-architecture.md`, production AxonStore deployment requires migrating existing `.ddx/beads.jsonl` corpora into Lakebase Postgres. The real importer is unimplemented.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;# ROOT CAUSE\u0026#xA;`cli/internal/bead/migrate.go` (function previously at `*Store.MigrateToAxon`, now folded into `*storeMigrator` per MIG bead) writes JSONL into a sidecar directory. The function does not connect to Postgres or invoke `AxonStore.Apply`/`AxonStore.Create`. Production deployment cannot use it to populate Lakebase.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;# PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. Implement a real importer in `cli/internal/bead/internal/storage/import_postgres.go` (or equivalent post-BL location). The importer:\u0026#xA;   - Reads `.ddx/beads.jsonl` (and `.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl` if present) — uses existing JSONL parser.\u0026#xA;   - For each bead, calls `axonStore.Create(ctx, \u0026amp;b)` to insert into Postgres. Idempotent on `ErrConflict` (skip + log).\u0026#xA;   - For each bead, appends events via `axonStore.Apply(ctx, id, AppendEventOp{...})` per TD-027 §13 vocabulary (events come from `Extra[\u0026#34;events\u0026#34;]` on the JSONL bead or from sidecar `.ddx/attachments/\u0026lt;bead\u0026gt;/events.jsonl`).\u0026#xA;   - Tracks progress, supports `--dry-run` (counts without writes), `--limit N` (batched migration).\u0026#xA;   - Verifies post-migration: read back beads from Postgres, assert field-for-field equality with source JSONL (sample-based for large corpora).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;2. Expose via `Migrator` interface (added in MIG): rename/replace `MigrateToAxon` with the real implementation; same method name, different (correct) behavior.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;3. Update `cli/cmd/bead_migrate.go` to support the importer with appropriate flags:\u0026#xA;   - `ddx bead migrate --to-axon --dry-run`\u0026#xA;   - `ddx bead migrate --to-axon --apply [--limit N]`\u0026#xA;   - `ddx bead migrate --to-axon --verify` (read-back + checksum)\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;4. Remove the deprecated JSONL-writing behavior. `ErrDeprecated` return from MIG bead is replaced by the real implementation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;# NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- Schema-versioning migration ladder (separate concern; deferred until first v1→v2 breaking change).\u0026#xA;- Real-wire integration test against actual Postgres — separate WIRE bead.\u0026#xA;- Continuous sync between JSONL and Postgres — not in scope; this is one-shot migration.\u0026#xA;- AxonStore itself — implemented in AX (`ddx-9c5bca8f`).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;# Acceptance criteria\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. New file `cli/internal/bead/internal/storage/import_postgres.go` (or equivalent) implements the JSONL→Postgres importer. Uses `axonStore.Create` + `axonStore.Apply` for inserts + event appends.\u0026#xA;2. Existing `Migrator.MigrateToAxon` method returns the real importer\u0026#39;s result (not `ErrDeprecated`).\u0026#xA;3. CLI flags wired: `--to-axon --dry-run`, `--to-axon --apply`, `--to-axon --verify`. Test: `TestImporter_DryRun_CountsOnly`, `TestImporter_Apply_WritesToPostgres`, `TestImporter_Verify_DetectsDrift`.\u0026#xA;4. Idempotency: re-running `--apply` on an already-imported corpus is a no-op (skips conflicts). Test: `TestImporter_Apply_Idempotent_OnReRun`.\u0026#xA;5. Field-fidelity: every JSONL bead field is preserved in Postgres, including `extra` preserved-keys. Test: `TestImporter_PreservesExtras`.\u0026#xA;6. Event ordering: events imported preserve monotonic `created_at` (TD-027 §11.2 invariant 8). Test: `TestImporter_PreservesEventOrdering`.\u0026#xA;7. Attachment migration: sidecar files under `.ddx/attachments/\u0026lt;bead\u0026gt;/` are uploaded to Unity Catalog Volumes (or local-equivalent for testing). Test: `TestImporter_MigratesAttachments`.\u0026#xA;8. Verification mode: post-import, sample N beads, read back from AxonStore, assert equality with source. Test: `TestImporter_Verify_RoundTripPassesOnCleanImport`.\u0026#xA;9. `cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./...` is green (with httptest-served Axon-shaped GraphQL endpoint or in-memory backend).\u0026#xA;10. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;# Labels\u0026#xA;phase:iterate, area:bead, area:axon, area:migration, kind:feature, spec:TD-027\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;# Parent + Deps\u0026#xA;Parent: ddx-8d747049\u0026#xA;Deps: ddx-9c5bca8f (AxonStore must exist), MIG bead (Migrator interface must exist).\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance/\u003e\n    \u003cnotes\u003e\ndecomposed into ddx-55a16aef, ddx-ff9300f9, ddx-b9884139\n    \u003c/notes\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003earea:axon, area:bead, area:migration, kind:feature, phase:iterate, spec:TD-027, triage:no-changes-unjustified\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-8d747049\" base-rev=\"842c1557ff38cabd32e0fe17f5dbcce501783f93\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260704T011321-22621c3e\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read them first. Ground decisions in repository state; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_ATTEMPT_ID":"20260704T011321-22621c3e","DDX_BEAD_DIR":"/Users/erik/Projects/ddx/.ddx","DDX_BEAD_ID":"ddx-53df5e2f","DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","GIT_CONFIG_GLOBAL":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-53df5e2f-20260704T011321-22621c3e/.ddx/executions/20260704T011321-22621c3e/embedded/git-global.cfg","GIT_CONFIG_SYSTEM":"/dev/null","PATH":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-53df5e2f-20260704T011321-22621c3e/.ddx/executions/20260704T011321-22621c3e/embedded/git-bin:/home/erik/.local/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/home/erik/.codex/tmp/arg0/codex-arg0Yu4YDA:/usr/local/cuda/bin:/home/erik/.jbang/bin:/home/erik/.opencode/bin:/Users/erik/.antigravity/antigravity/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/shims:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-subrepo/lib:/Applications/SnowSQL.app/Contents/MacOS:/home/erik/.local/share/coursier/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-fuzzy/bin:/home/erik/go/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/scripts:/home/erik/.cargo/bin:/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin:/usr/games:/usr/local/games:/snap/bin:/Users/erik/Library/Application Support/JetBrains/Toolbox/scripts:/Users/erik/Library/Application Support/Coursier/bin:/home/erik/.lmstudio/bin:/home/erik/.cache/lm-studio/bin:/Users/erik/.cache/lm-studio/bin:/Users/erik/.lmstudio/bin","attempt_id":"20260704T011321-22621c3e","base_rev":"842c1557ff38cabd32e0fe17f5dbcce501783f93","bead_id":"ddx-53df5e2f","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260704T011321-22621c3e","correlation_id":"ddx-53df5e2f:20260704T011321-22621c3e","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260704T011321-22621c3e/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"4513fdb2261afd082b594b8c2c536c6d85f4f5c851134ba4c9c7f7e087dbb5fb","role":"implementer"